title._content: Mound "Bonhög" with stone chamber tomb, Hammarlöv, Skåne, Sweden

description._content: Man at the excavation of the "Bonhög" Mound from the Bronze Age, with a stone chamber tomb, The mound was excavated in 1892 by Oscar Montelius, archaeologist and Director General of the Swedish National Heritage Board in 1907-1913. He could be the photographer. Man vid utgrävningen av gravhögen "Bonhög" från bronsåldern, med en stenkammargrav. Högen undersöktes 1892 av Oscar Montelius, arkeolog och riksantikvarie 1907-1913. Han kan vara fotografen. Parish (socken): Hammarlöv Province (landskap): Skåne Municipality (kommun): Trelleborg County (län): Skåne Photograph by: Unknown Date: 1892 Format: Glass plate negative Persistent URL: http://www.kms.raa.se/cocoon/bild/show-image.html?id=16001000181104 Read more about the photo database (in english): www.kms.raa.se/cocoon/bild/about.html
